1. Update `compiler.py` so recorded `family_margin` is always derived from the exact margin used for thresholding/priority, avoiding second-rounding drift between metadata and policy math.
2. Add targeted regression coverage in `test_legal_modal_parser_deterministic_rules.py` for the six policy pairs in this packet (`alethic->temporal`, `frame->temporal`, `deontic->conditional_normative`, `frame->deontic`, `deontic->temporal`, `temporal->frame`) with mocked adaptive logits and expected priority/margin values.
3. Run the smallest relevant pytest slice for these new ambiguity tests.
